# HRMS + InHouse Chat — Windsurf AI Rules
# Version: 4.0 | Stack: Next.js 14 + Express.js + Poly-Database
# These rules apply to ALL files in the project.

## PROJECT IDENTITY
You are working on an internal HRMS (Human Resource Management System) with an
integrated InHouse Chat tool for a 20-person company. This is a monolithic PWA.
Priority: HRMS features FIRST, Chat SECOND.

## STACK OVERVIEW
- Frontend:  Next.js 14 (App Router), TypeScript, Tailwind CSS, shadcn/ui
- Backend:   Express.js 5, TypeScript, Socket.io
- Databases: PostgreSQL (Prisma ORM), MongoDB Atlas (Mongoose), Supabase (Auth + Storage + Realtime)
- Cache:     Redis (ioredis + BullMQ)
- Monorepo:  pnpm + Turborepo
- Testing:   Vitest + Playwright
- Deploy:    Docker + Nginx + PM2 (free tools only — NO paid services in dev)

## ABSOLUTE RULES — NEVER VIOLATE

### TypeScript
- ALWAYS use `strict: true`. NEVER use `any`. Use `unknown` + type narrowing instead.
- NEVER use type assertions (`as SomeType`) at module boundaries — add a comment if truly needed.
- ALWAYS derive TypeScript types from Zod schemas: `type X = z.infer<typeof xSchema>`. Never duplicate type definitions.
- ALL exported functions must have explicit return types.
- Use `type` for data shapes, `interface` only for declaration merging.

### React / Next.js
- ALWAYS use named exports for components. `default export` only for Next.js page.tsx / layout.tsx (framework requirement).
- NEVER use `export default function MyComponent` in non-page files.
- Pages (`page.tsx`) are Server Components by default. Add `'use client'` only for interactivity.
- NEVER fetch data in `useEffect`. Use Server Components or TanStack Query (`useQuery`).
- NEVER use raw `<img>` tags. Always use `next/image`.
- NEVER use `<a>` for internal navigation. Always use `next/link`.
- Components must be under 150 lines. Split if longer.
- One component per file. No multi-component files.
- Lazy-load heavy components: `dynamic(() => import(...), { ssr: false })` for charts, PDFs, rich text.

### CSS / Tailwind
- Tailwind utility classes ONLY. NO CSS Modules. NO styled-components. NO emotion. NO inline `style={{}}` (except truly dynamic values).
- NEVER hardcode hex/rgb colors in className strings. Use CSS variable tokens defined in globals.css.
- NEVER use `!important`.
- ALWAYS write Tailwind classes in order: layout → position → box model → typography → visual → transition → responsive (sm/md/lg) → state (hover/focus/disabled).
- Use `cn()` from `@/lib/utils` for conditional class merging.
- Use `cva()` from `class-variance-authority` for component variants — never ternary chains for variants.
- Dark mode: every `bg-`, `text-`, `border-` class needs a `dark:` counterpart, or must use a CSS variable token.

### API / Express
- Middleware order is FIXED: authenticate → requireRole → validate(zodSchema) → handler → next(error)
- NEVER call `res.status(500).json(...)` inline. Always `next(error)` to the global error handler.
- ALWAYS use `AppError` class for thrown errors: `throw new AppError('CODE', statusCode)`.
- API response shape is FIXED — success: `{ success: true, data: ... }`, error: `{ success: false, error: { code, message } }`.
- Paginate ALL list endpoints. Never return unbounded arrays.
- ALWAYS use `Promise.all([])` for independent async operations. Never sequential awaits.

### Database
- PostgreSQL (Prisma): HRM data only. ALWAYS select specific fields — never `findMany()` with no `select`. ALWAYS add `@@index` for filtered/sorted columns in schema.
- MongoDB (Mongoose): Chat, notifications, activity feed, audit logs only. ALWAYS use `.lean()` for read-only queries. Use cursor-based pagination for chat messages.
- Supabase: Auth + Storage + Realtime only. ALWAYS use signed URLs for private file access.
- Redis: Ephemeral data only. Presence TTL, rate limits, cache, BullMQ queues.
- Cache pattern: check Redis → DB miss → store with TTL → invalidate on mutation.

### Security
- NEVER trust role/permissions from client request body or headers.
- NEVER commit secrets or credentials. Always use environment variables.
- ALWAYS validate file uploads with `file-type` package (real MIME detection, not extension).
- ALWAYS sanitize filenames: `path.basename(name).replace(/[^a-zA-Z0-9._-]/g, '_')`.
- MongoDB queries: ALWAYS validate ObjectId with `isValidObjectId()`. NEVER interpolate user input into query operators.
- Payroll runs are IMMUTABLE after lock — never allow updates to locked payroll.

### Performance
- Use `Promise.all()` for parallel DB queries.
- Redis-cache expensive queries (leave balance, org chart) with appropriate TTL.
- Socket.io: ALWAYS use room-based emit (`io.to(roomId).emit`). NEVER broadcast to all sockets.
- Throttle typing indicators on client (2000ms). Debounce typing stop (3000ms).

### Notifications
- Push uses `web-push` with VAPID keys. NEVER use Firebase FCM (paid/Google dependency).
- iOS PWA push: `Notification.requestPermission()` MUST be inside a user gesture handler (onClick).
- Store `PushSubscription` per user+device in MongoDB. One user can have multiple device subscriptions.
- ALWAYS enqueue push/email via BullMQ worker — never send synchronously in request handler.

### Git / Commits
- Branch naming: `feat/`, `fix/`, `chore/`, `refactor/`, `docs/` prefixes.
- Commits follow Conventional Commits: `feat(module): description`.
- One concern per PR. No mixed features + fixes.

### Toolchain — FREE ONLY
- NEVER suggest paid tools, services, or libraries.
- Approved free alternatives: Vitest (not Jest paid plans), Playwright (not Cypress paid), DBeaver (not TablePlus paid), Uptime Kuma (not Datadog), Sentry free tier, Grafana (self-hosted).

